<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Line-Height applied to 'none'</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#leading" />
        <meta name="flags" content="font" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Line-Height can be applied to 'none' level elements." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                width: 100px;
                height: 100px;
                background-color: green;
                color: Green;
                margin: 100px;
            }
            #d2
            {
                display: none;
                line-height: 100px;
                font-size: 72pt;
                font-family: Arial;
                background-color: red;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if a green box is visible and there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <div id="d2">Filler Text</div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>